        <headline>Flood Advisory issued July 15 at 9:49AM EDT until July 15 at 2:00PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Runoff from yesterday's heavy rain caused the Bronx River
to rise to moderate flood stage of around 3.7 ft early this
morning. Water levels are slowly falling, but the river remains in
minor flood stage.

* WHERE...A portion of southeast New York, including the following
county, Bronx.

* WHEN...Until 200 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Water over Bronx River Parkway due to elevated stream
flow on the Bronx River.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 943 AM EDT, The river has crested and will continue to
subside below minor flood stage of 3 ft through this
afternoon. Flooding should subside on the Bronx River Parkway
once water levels fall below 3 ft.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
East Tremont, Woodlawn and Fordham.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.

Stay away or be swept away. River banks and culverts can become
unstable and unsafe.</instruction>
